Rotate the coordinate system.

The [transform](/documentation/tags/transform.html) methods are used to position
objects in your application. You can rotate about a particular axis (x,y,z) or
about an arbitrary axis of rotation. See the [examples](#examples) section below
for usage.

{:.alert.alert-info}
Be sure to wrap `rotate` calls with `pushMatrix()` and `popMatrix()` to restore
the environment to its original state. Otherwise, all subsequent rendering calls
will be rotated.

See the [coordinate system tutorial](/tutorials/coordinate-transformations.html)
for more information.

### syntax

~~~ python
rotateX(rx)
rotateY(ry)
rotateZ(rz)
rotate(angle, axis)
~~~

### parameters

rx    | angle of rotation about the x-axis
ry    | angle of rotation about the y-axis
rz    | angle of rotation about the z-axis
angle | angle of rotation about arbitrary axis
axis  | axis of rotation

### examples

#### cylinder rotated 90 degrees about the x-axis


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "rotate", "cylinder-rotated-90-degrees-about-the-x-axis.png" %>


~~~ python
def display():
   lighting(False)

   cylinder(1.5, 6.0)

   rotateX(90)
   color(green)
   cylinder(1.5, 6.0)
~~~

